  "texts": [
    "Specifically, specificity can be calculated using Eq.",
    "( 8):Specificity = TN TN + FP.",
    "(8)The value of specificity ranges between 0 and 1, with a higher value indicating a stronger ability of the model to recognize negative samples.",
    "Performance comparison and analysis Overall evaluationTo quantify the performance of different models, we conducted a comprehensive evaluation of 24 representative polyp segmentation models, including 1) 18 CNN-based models: U-Net [20], UNet++ [101], SFA [22], PraNet [26], ACSNet [25], MSEG [30], EU-Net [31], SANet [8], MSNet [9], UACANet-S [34], UACANet-L [34], C2FNet [35], DCRNet [53], BDG-Net [50], CaraNet [44], EFA-Net [102], CFA-Net [75], and M2SNet [103], and 2) six Transformer-based methods: Polyp-PVT [33], HSNet [46], DuAT [62], ESFPNet [72], FeDNet [70], and SAM-based poly segmentation model (with three different backbones, i.e., SAM-B, SAM-H, and SAM-L [104]).",
    "First, we individually evaluated the performance of the aforementioned 24 models on SPE, SEN, Dice, IoU, S α, F β, E φ, and MAE metrics across five public datasets (ETIS-LaribPolypDB [91], CVC-ColonDB [5], CVC-ClinicDB [7], CVC-300 [92], and Kvasir-SEG [93])."
  ],
